<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She celebrated her 39th birthday on Monday at a swanky meal with friends in Chelsea.</p>

<p>But Ashley Roberts showed no sign of her late night as she left Heart Radio in central London on Tuesday.</p>

<p>The Pussycat Dolls star looked radiant in a black and white buttoned dress as she strutted out of Global Studios. </p>

<p>Glowing: Ashley Roberts looked radiant in a black and white buttoned dress as she left Heart Radio after a late night birthday bash on Tuesday</p>

<p>She flaunted her tanned and toned legs in a pair of black patent stilettos and carried a matching black handbag with her.</p>

<p>The singing sensation wore her blonde tresses in a poker straight style and looked every inch the star in black cat-eye sunglasses. </p>

<p>The black mini dress featured gold buttons along with white edging and belt which showed off Ashley's svelte frame.</p>

<p>Stepping out: The Pussycat Doll star looked sensational as she strutted out of Global Studios after her show </p>

<p>Fashionista: She flaunted her tanned and toned legs in a pair of black patent stilettos and carried a matching black handbag with her</p>

<p>On Monday night Ashley stepped out for dinner at La Famiglia in Chelsea to mark the milestone of her 39th birthday. </p>

<p>She looked pretty in a girly flowery dress as she left the eatery with friends carrying a bag of presents.  </p>

<p>Earlier in the day, the singing sensation treated her Instagram followers to a racy new bikini snap to mark the occasion. </p>

<p>Strutting her stuff: The singing sensation wore her blonde tresses in a poker straight style and looked every inch the star in black cat-eye sunglasses</p>

<p>Stylish: The black mini dress featured gold buttons and white edging and belt which showed off Ashley's svelte frame</p>

<p>Beautiful: She showed no signs of her late night as she stepped out in the balmy September temperatures</p>

<p>The blonde beauty showed off her incredible physique in a matching two-piece while posing for the playful image. </p>

<p>Referencing her birthday and Britain's unseasonably warm September weather in an accompanying caption, she wrote: 'Ring Ring: Alexa says it’s 30 degrees and my birthday hunni’s. Thank you for all your lovely messages!!!'  </p>

<p>The post prompted an inevitable wave of positive comments from fans, among them former Strictly Come Dancing champion Stacey Dooley, who wrote:  'WELL WELL WELL, happy bday sis.' </p>

